.TH "t4_enable_vi_params" 9 "t4_enable_vi_params" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t4_enable_vi_params \- enable/disable a virtual interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t4_enable_vi_params
.BI "(struct adapter *adap "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mbox "  ","
.BI "unsigned int viid "  ","
.BI "bool rx_en "  ","
.BI "bool tx_en "  ","
.BI "bool dcb_en "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adap" 12
the adapter
.IP "mbox" 12
mailbox to use for the FW command
.IP "viid" 12
the VI id
.IP "rx_en" 12
1=enable Rx, 0=disable Rx
.IP "tx_en" 12
1=enable Tx, 0=disable Tx
.IP "dcb_en" 12
1=enable delivery of Data Center Bridging messages.

Enables/disables a virtual interface.  Note that setting DCB Enable
only makes sense when enabling a Virtual Interface ...
